The Five principles of Lean

  1) specify value
  2) Map the value stream
  3) Create Flow
  4) Respond to customer demand
  5) Pursue Perfection
  
Key Takeaways:

Lean is a method for improving processes by maximizing customer value and minimizing waste.
Lean is supported by two pillars: continuous improvement and respect for people.
Lean achieves its goals through five principles: (1) specify value, (2) map the value stream, (3) improve flow, (4) respond to customer demand (or "pull"), and (5) pursue perfection.
